---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import FeatureBlock from '@components/FeatureBlock.astro';
import VisualPreview from '@components/VisualPreview.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Zaratük Consulting"
  description="Zaratük Consulting builds Power BI custom visuals for the analysts and BI developers behind the reports everyone relies on."
>
  <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-12 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.95fr_1.05fr] lg:px-8 lg:items-center">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-forest-700">About Zaratük</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-normal text-forest-950 sm:text-6xl">
          Power BI visuals for the operational side of analytics.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-slate-600">
          We build pbiviz products for the Power BI developers and analysts who care about keeping their reports healthy, accurate, and worth trusting. Data health, pipeline status, and quality signals — right inside the report your team already lives in.
        </p>
      </div>
      <VisualPreview />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-rule bg-slate-50 py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-forest-700">Product direction</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-normal text-forest-950 sm:text-4xl">
          We build custom visuals that make Power BI more useful for operational control.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
        <FeatureBlock
          eyebrow="Health Signals"
          title="Operational Signals"
          body="Visuals that surface data freshness, missing values, and anomalies — so you know your report is telling the truth before anyone else notices it isn't."
        />
        <FeatureBlock
          eyebrow="Built-in Confidence"
          title="Embedded Validation"
          body="Custom visuals that keep validation rules visible beside the measures and dimensions you built, so your report keeps earning its reputation."
        />
        <FeatureBlock
          eyebrow="Report Integrity"
          title="Reporting Trust"
          body="Focused visuals that make it clear whether your dashboard is ready to drive decisions — or needs your attention first."
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-rule bg-white py-16">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.2fr] lg:px-8">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-forest-700">Why Power BI</p>
        <h2 class="mt-4 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-normal text-forest-950">
          Power BI can be more than the final report.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-base leading-8 text-slate-600">
        <p>
          The analysts and BI developers behind the best Power BI reports carry a quiet responsibility — when something breaks, they're the first to know and the first to fix it. Our goal is to put the right signals directly inside the report canvas, so you can catch data issues, validate key fields, and stay confident in what your report is showing.
        </p>
        <p>
          That means building visuals with clear behavior, practical configuration, and a strong focus on the daily work of the people who built the report everybody depends on.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
